13/03/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The trial of 11 Bosnian Serbs, charged with genocide in the Srebrenica region during the war, will begin at the BiH Court on 4 May, according to an announcement Friday (10 March).
The 11 are charged in connection with the murders of over 100 Bosniaks in the villages of Kravica and Sandici on 13 July 1995.
The BiH court confirmed the indictment -- the first domestic case dealing with genocide -- last December.
(PBS BiH, NTV Hayat, Fena - 10/03/06)
